dataCsv.Site_Description: The Nelson sits upright on the bottom with a very intact hull and the bow and forecastle deck broken off. The cargo of coal is visible in the holds. Many on site artifacts and machinery include two wood stock anchors, manual bilge pump, steam bilge pump, three capstans, windlass, deck winch, donkey boiler, broken masts, booms, gaffs, stove, ships wheel, steering box, rudder, boom cradle, boom tables, centerboard winch, catheads.
